# üöÄ Action Elements Demo - New Syntax

This demo showcases the new action element syntax in FormDown.

## Basic Action Elements

### Submit Button
@[submit "Send Message"]

### Reset Button  
@[reset "Clear Form"]

### Custom Button with JavaScript
@[button "Calculate Total" onclick="calculateTotal()"]

### Image Button
@[image "Submit Order" src="/images/submit-btn.png" alt="Submit Order"]

---

## Complete Form Example

### Customer Registration

@form[action="/register" method="POST"]

@first_name(First Name): [text required minlength=2]
@last_name(Last Name): [text required minlength=2]
@email(Email Address): [email required]
@phone(Phone Number): [tel]
@birth_date(Date of Birth): [date max="2010-12-31"]

@interests(Your Interests): [checkbox options="Technology,Sports,Music,Travel,Gaming"]
@newsletter(Newsletter): [checkbox content="Subscribe to our weekly newsletter"]

@[submit "Create Account" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg"]
@[reset "Clear Form" class="btn btn-outline-secondary"]
@[button "Save as Draft" class="btn btn-warning" onclick="saveDraft()"]

---

## Action Elements with Advanced Styling

### Form with Custom Button Classes

@name: [text required placeholder="Your name"]
@email: [email required placeholder="your@email.com"]

@[submit "Submit Application" class="btn btn-success btn-lg shadow-lg" data-submit="true"]
@[button "Preview" class="btn btn-info" onclick="showPreview()" data-preview="true"]
@[reset "Start Over" class="btn btn-danger btn-sm"]

---

## Mixed Syntax Compatibility

You can mix the new action syntax with legacy syntax:

@username: [text required]
@password: [password required]

<!-- New syntax (recommended) -->
@[submit "Sign In"]

<!-- Legacy syntax (still supported) -->  
@forgot_password: [button label="Forgot Password?" onclick="forgotPassword()"]

---

## Image Buttons

### Upload Form with Image Submit

@files(Upload Files): [file multiple accept="image/*,application/pdf"]
@description: [textarea rows=3 placeholder="Describe your files..."]

@[image "Upload Files" src="/images/upload-btn.png" width="150" height="40"]
@[button "Cancel Upload" class="btn-cancel" onclick="cancelUpload()"]

